    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 defines a single standard test configuration and regulatory precedent supports its sufficiency for 510(k) submissions. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10% across three independent FEA environments and two test laboratories. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the signature workflow is pending and no digital signature has been applied.",
